Description: Fragment of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Oval handle to sharpish turn. Rectangular stamp with grape cluster symbol. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Preobably drawn by Petrie (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.175, 2). Name Themison. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, CEALEX GAB 1077?
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1060)
